Photo by @amivitale. Breaking news for one of Africaâ€™s most iconic species: On December 8 2016 the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) moved giraffes two categories down the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species from "Least Concern" to "Vulnerable." The IUCN reports that the new designation was due to the giraffe's dramatic 40 percent decline since 1985. But luckily some researchers have been paying attention to the declining trends for the last decade or more and are poised to help increase the priority of conservation interventions for these gentle giants. Learn more about this important work: bit.ly/GiraffesinPeril 
